        Create the parameters necessary for confirming a PaymentIntent while attaching a PaymentMethod that already exits.
        Parameters:
        paymentMethodId - the ID of the PaymentMethod that is being attached to the PaymentIntent being confirmed
        clientSecret - client secret from the PaymentIntent being confirmed
        returnUrl - the URL the customer should be redirected to after the authorization process
        savePaymentMethod - Set to true to save this PaymentIntent’s payment method to the associated Customer, if the payment method is not already attached. This parameter only applies to the payment method passed in the same request or the current payment method attached to the PaymentIntent and must be specified again if a new payment method is added.
